<TITLE> Chief bucks PKSF micro-credit legacy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 20 (bdnews24.com)The PKSF chief says they have walked the wrong path over the last 20 years, having reduced their role to only giving micro-credit even though they were to assist rural job generation . Qazi Kholiquzzaman Ahmad, chairman of the Palli Karma-Sahayak Foundation (PKSF), came down heavily on micro-credit questioning its potency. Speaking to journalists on Thursday, the PKSF chairman referred to his organisation's long practice of disbursing micro-credit through selected organisations since its creation in 1990. Kholiquzzaman said, "For the last 20 years, PKSF has deviated from its true path and concentrated on micro-credit only." Introducing a new initiative of the foundation, closer to what its name suggestsrural employment generation the PKSF chief, also a noted economist, said it was high time to evaluate whether the foundation's main goal had been achieved, regardless of the phenomenal loan recovery rate of 99 percent. The new initiative, ENRICH  short for Enhancing Resources and Increasing Capacities of Poor Housholds Towards Elimination of their Poverty  targets 55,000 families. "We have now taken steps towards combined household-based development," said Kholiquzzaman, explaining that this new initiative would put much emphasis on education and healthcare. This project titled 'Total Household Development' was undertaken on May 3 and will be implemented at 21 union councils at first, through 21 partner agencies. Evidently reiterating his previous position on the impotence of micro-credit in poverty reduction, Kholiquzzaman said, "No family or country can progress, based on loans alone." Thus, he reasoned, PKSF initiatives would target 'asset creation' and enhancing individual capabilities for sustainable poverty eradication. Until now, the foundation has enlisted 1.05 crore families under its loan programmes. Of them, 83 lakh benefic
